summary: Apple (NASDAQ: AAPL) was founded in 1976, and in just four short years it went from a humble start-up with a dream of producing personal computers to a publicly listed company.  It even has the support of Warren Buffett, who is widely regarded as one of the best investors in history.  Apple is the largest single stock holding for his conglomerate, Berkshire Hathaway, which now owns a position worth approximately $115 billion.

headline: Tech’s Bill Is Coming Due. Investors Aren’t the Only Ones Who Will Pay.
summary: Tech companies went on a spending binge to satisfy new pandemic demand. Then came the reopening and the rate hikes. Now, the bill is due.
